# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Pulse_Brain — engine .gitignore
# This repo is the ENGINE: it ships architecture and templates only.
# Live data is EXCLUDED by default — the engine ships templates and code only.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Live data (never in the engine) ──
# The engine ships templates, not content. Instance data lives in Pulse-{{OWNER}}-Brain.
/instance/
/vault/
Pulse-*-Brain/
data/
**/data/
*.live.md

# Model & Retrieval Substrate (S17) — embeddings are DERIVED live content (a lossy,
# possibly-invertible projection of canon) + the pulled model is runtime state. The
# engine ships the substrate CODE only; the store/vectors/model never get committed.
# `*.shard` catches a store wherever `--store` points it, not only the default path.
.claude/substrate/store/
**/substrate/store/
**/substrate/**/shards/
*.shard
*.vec
*.faiss
*.ann
*.safetensors
*.onnx
*.gguf
.pulse-model-cache/
**/.pulse-model-cache/

# ── Secrets & credentials ──
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*_secret*
*_credentials*
*apikey*
*token*.json

# ── Claude Code internals (settings are environment-specific) ──
.claude/settings.json
.claude/settings.local.json

# ── Obsidian instance noise (if the dir is ever opened as a vault) ──
# The engine ships no Obsidian config; that's per-instance. Ignore it all.
.obsidian/
.trash/

# ── Python ──
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ── Node ──
node_modules/
dist/

# ── macOS ──
.DS_Store
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes

# ── Editors ──
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
